-- 2012-04-21T11:15:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-21/bondcare-plans-bid-for-four-seasons-health-care-sky-reports.html
Bondcare Group, a U.K. care-home
provider, plans to bid for Four Seasons Health Care Group Ltd.,
Britainâ€™s largest nursing home operator,  Sky News   reported .  Four Seasons Health Care, which is controlled by lenders
including  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS) , has asked bidders to
submit offers by early next week and may be sold for as much as
900 million pounds ($1.5 billion), Sky News reported on its
website, without saying where it got the information.  Deutsche Bank AG, Gleacher Shacklock and Rothschild are
advising Four Seasons Health Care, Sky News said. None of the
parties involved in the auction was available for comment, Sky
News reported.  Melanie Smith, a spokeswoman for Bondcare, declined to
comment when called by Bloomberg News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
